NON-GAUSSIAN — Kakeya-style / non-Gaussian shaping has measurable space above Shannon i.i.d. Gaussian bound. Research paths (iii), (iv), (vi) from HANDOFF §5.8 are worth pursuing.

Triggered gates:
  • kurtosis: excess |kurt - 3|_max = 0.840 > 0.5
  • W_2: max per-layer mean-over-dim W_2/σ = 0.652 > 0.05
  • score: max per-layer mean-over-dim rel score dev = 0.125 > 0.1
  • isotropy: max per-layer variance ratio (max/min) = 4.711 > 1.5

